STORY #1:  A CASE OF QEYNOS VENGEANCE<br>
<br>
&quot;The mark of the immature man is that he wants to die<br>
nobly for a cause, whereas the mark of the mature man<br>
is that he wants to live humbly for one.&quot;  --W. Stekel<br>
<br>
How could I, Rhaxalygen, live humbly for vengeance? <br>
<br>
I had joined up with the League of Antonican Bards to<br>
disguise my real purpose for living in Qeynos--staying<br>
there long enough to kill Grennet Stormhand, a Knight<br>
of Thunder. I had a very dark score to settle with him. <br>
<br>
Normally, I would leave the Paladins of Karana alone, <br>
but this one, unfortunately, had killed my own brother, <br>
Sirrius Schwarzek. &quot;Black&quot; was the first part of our<br>
surname, blackness like the sky at midnight, and &quot;zek&quot;, <br>
of course, referred to Rallos Zek, the Warlord that our<br>
entire family had fearlessly served.  Black War! That<br>
was us. Our purpose was to give our lives in combat.    <br>
<br>
Our battle deeds were viewed as noble, except by one Grennet Stormhand. He held a grudge against us for our one flaw, the one mistake we had all made, when we charged into Blackburrow and ended up killing dozens<br>
of hapless and innocent adventurers by mistake.   <br>
<br>
It wasn't our fault, though!  The gnolls swarmed on them!<br>
<br>
Sirrius was the leader of our hunting party, the ill-fated<br>
&quot;Blackburrow Butchers&quot;, as we were then called.  This was not an ignoble name.  Rather, it was an honor, for <br>
the Sabertooths of Blackburrow, who worshipped our<br>
enemy, the Plague Lord, were Qeynos' biggest foes. <br>
<br>
So, here we are: Sirrius, my brother, and I, and our<br>
father, the Champion, Vallon Schwarzek, storming <br>
into the caves of the Gnolls without a second thought.<br>
<br>
&quot;TRAIN, TRAIN, TRAIN!&quot; we heard some people scream. <br>
<br>
Instantly, a swarm of gnolls came thundering down upon the adventurers in the cave, stinking up the air with their putrid breath and ever-present piles of dung!  Sirrius, it<br>
seemed, had stirred up a whole nest of these beasts<br>
through his presence, and so Grennet Stormhand, <br>
when he heard of the news, blamed my brother for the<br>
untimely deaths of several bystanders, including four<br>
Thunder Knights in training.  Grennet was very angry!<br>
<br>
Thus, it came to pass that he slew my brother for his recklessness.  I, since I had not been the leader that day, was not punished, but the Knights of Thunder let<br>
me know it would only be a matter of time before the<br>
hot arrogance of my brother seeped its way into me! <br>
<br>
Too late.  It already has. <br>
<br>
So, I seek vengeance for the death of Sirrius Schwarzek,<br>
and as for me, I serve War, and no other futile cause! <br>
<br>
Yours, <br>
Rhaxalygen Schwarzek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sweetumsofakanon>Sweetums of Ak Anon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/5/03 12:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.leagueofshadows.net/sigs/Sweetums1.gif width=90 height=90></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Three Stories--YOU PICK my next Avatar!!!</span><hr size=1> Sorrys tas interrupts, but mes gots tas votes for da gnomes.  Yoos bes gnome.  Everybudy shuds bes gnome like mes.  *nods*<br>
