<br>
Bellatrix kissed the diseased blade of her Scourge<br>
Knight Saber, once, near its razor-sharp point. <br>
She knew what such a sword had cost her--her<br>
good standing with the citizens of Qeynos, the <br>
respect of noble Paladins and Clerics, and,<br>
most of all, her neutral faction with all Norrath. <br>
<br>
Everyone had loved her when she was seriously ill.<br>
Now, thanks to Bertoxxulous, she was well, yet<br>
almost all of Qeynos spurned her company. <br>
<br>
She had been blessed with Erythrosepsis, a<br>
plague of terminally diseased blood, which had<br>
caused weakness, bouts of unconsciousness,<br>
and the most terrible side effect of near-deadly fever. <br>
Back when she was a good and humble citizen of<br>
Qeynos, preparing to enter the maidservant's trade,<br>
Bellatrix had thought she had been utterly cursed. <br>
<br>
Now she knew better. Bertoxxulous had given<br>
her disease in order to teach her to appreciate<br>
health--the health that only he, the Plague Lord,<br>
was prepared to bestow upon young Bellatrix. <br>
<br>
For a price. Bellatrix ventured boldly into the sewers. <br>
<br>
She declared, &quot;I have gone to Nife. I have knelt before<br>
his highest priestesses, Jahnda and the paladin Suuspa Clanim, and all they could give me was an admonition to remain meek and modest, for the gods had willed my plagued blood. Similarly, I have gone to all the Knights<br>
of Thunder, together with Karana's Clerics,  and they, too, said that Karana had destined my blood to remain<br>
impure, so that I would learn the value of healing arts.<br>
<br>
None of them would relieve me. Will you, Bloodsabres?&quot;<br>
<br>
They nodded. Every one of them was prepared to accept this young maidservant-in-training as a servant of their<br>
own, sentimental platitudes and admonitions be cursed!<br>
<br>
&quot;We hear you, Bellatrix,&quot; said Nomaria Doseniar, high<br>
female Cleric of Bertoxxulous, &quot;and we'll answer your<br>
tortured cries. Your disease is a blessing of the Plague<br>
Lord, Norrath praise him, and this means that if you <br>
surrender to the shadows that have haunted and chased you for your entire life, you shall be well and strong!&quot; <br>
<br>
Bellatrix nodded. It was her last chance, so it seemed. <br>
Her heart, too, had always had a trembling side that yearned to embrace the Plaguebringer and all his ways. <br>
&quot;If disease comes directly from Bertoxxulous,&quot; she had<br>
thought deep in her secret heart, when all of Norrath was<br>
asleep, &quot;then perhaps he will liberate me from my Erythrosepsis if I will but serve him.&quot; Thus she did...<br>
<br>
...and all of Qeynos wished her exile or death itself! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhaxalygen>Rhaxalygen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 282<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/11/03 7:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Story #3</span><hr size=1> STORY #3: A TEENY PALADIN<br>
<br>
Zatatine was a hot-blooded Gnome, with a heart<br>
a thousand times stouter than Brell's Blessed Ale,<br>
yet no one would take her seriously when she told<br>
them she was a Paladin. A holy knight--so small?!<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, I am a holy knight,&quot; she would declare, <br>
holding her platinum-blonde head high, her voice<br>
sounding exactly like Brittany from &quot;Alvin and the<br>
Chipmunks&quot;, &quot;and I can heal you right now!&quot; <br>
<br>
She did heal, as best as she could, though her<br>
natural Wisdom was exceedingly low. Lay on Hands<br>
was her bread and butter, and mana be darned, Zata<br>
did her absolute darndest to make sure all the kobolds<br>
in Steamfont met her small, sneaky, slashing sword!<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm ready for anything!&quot;, she'd declare to all Norrath.<br>
<br>
Anything, of course, except an unexpected kidnapping!<br>
<br>
She'd been shanghai'ed by [name of guild], and she served [name of guild] until her final days, even though<br>
[name of guild]'s opinion of Brell Serilis was decidedly<br>
low. Seeing no way of escape for her small self, Zata<br>
decided that humility and serving her captors with <br>
kindness were more in tune with the ideals of the<br>
Duke of Below than was killing them for the Underfoot.<br>
<br>
Plus, they gave her lots and lots and lots of protection.<br>
<br>
Small paladins needed big guardians! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elyta@firionavie>Elyta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>Illusions of a Storm<b></span><br>  Posts: 408<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/14/03 9:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Story #3</span><hr size=1> hmm... story 3....<br>
